oximation of Circles by Curvature continuous Bezier Curves by Tor Dokken Morten Daehlen Tom Lyche and Knut Morken in Computer Aided Geometric Design volume numbers combined June pages Elsevier Science Publishers North Holland How to order standards The American National Standards Institute sells ANSI standards and also ISO international Their sales office is at mailing address is Broadway NY NY It helps if you have the complete name and Some useful numbers to know CGM Computer Graphics Metafile is ISO GKS Graphical Kernel System is ANSI PHIGS Programmer's Hierarchical Interactive Graphics System is ANSI IGES is ASME ANSI Language bindings are often separate but related numbers for example the GKS FORTRAN binding is Standards in progress are made available at key milestones to solicit comments from the graphical public this includes you ANSI can let you know where to order them most are available from Global Engineering at How to FTP by There are a number of sites that archive the Usenet sources newsgroups and make them available via an email query You send a message to an automated server saying something like send fbm and a few hours or days later you get the file in the In addition there is at least one FTP by mail Send mail to saying help and it will tell you how to use Note that this service has at times been turned off due to How to tell whether a point is within a planar Consider a ray originating at the point of interest and continuing to If it crosses an odd number of polygon edges along the way the point is within the If the ray crosses an even number of edges the point is either outside the polygon or within an interior hole formed from intersecting polygon This idea is known in the trade as the Jordan curve theorem see Eric Haines' article in Glassner's ray tracing book above for more information including treatment of special Another method is to sum the absolute angles from the point to all the vertices on the If the sum is pi the point is inside if the sum is the point is However this method is about an order of magnitude slower than the previous method because evaluating the trigonometric functions is usually quite Code for both methods plus barycentric triangle testing can be found in the Ray Tracing News available from pub Graphics RTNews How to tessellate a One simple way is to do recursive subdivision into The base of the recursion is an octahedron and then each level divides each triangle into four smaller Jon Leech has posted a nice routine called that generates the It's available for FTP on and Specific references on ray tracing and global Rick Speer maintains a cross indexed ray tracing bibliography Highlights of this edition i more than citations spanning the period from through November ' ii papers from all Siggraph Graphics Interface Eurographics CG International and Ausgraph proceedings through December ' iii all citations keyworded for easy lookup iv cross indices by keyword and author v glossary of the keywords The bib is in the form of a PostScript The printout is pages Below is a list of ftp sites and the dirs that contain the It's named and is compressed at most sites Site Dir graphics graphics bib pub Graphics pub papers pub sci papers graphics graphics papers Eric Haines maintains ray tracing and radiosity global illumination These are in refer format and so can be searched electronically a simple awk script to search for keywords is included with each The bibliographies are available at most of the sites listed above and the most current versions are maintained at pub Graphics Papers as and Tom Wilson has collected over abstracts from ray tracing related research papers and The information is essentially in plaintext and Latex and troff formatting programs are This collection is available at most of the sites above as SIGGRAPH information online from Steve Cunningham and Ralph Orlick ACM SIGGRAPH announces its online information site at This site now provides SIGGRAPH information via both ano